00:43:48,747 --> 00:43:50,828
in the north, we have the stealth one.

669
00:43:51,846 --> 00:43:57,330
Green paths are play styles, the numbers are entrances to the level, and the letters are

670
00:43:57,450 --> 00:44:00,052
exits or goals leading to a lower floor.

671
00:44:01,433 --> 00:44:07,318
Just as before, blue zones are discovery beats, and orange ones exploration, though, admittedly,

672
00:44:07,558 --> 00:44:10,641
I did not think about them like that at the time of the making of that blockout.

673
00:44:12,082 --> 00:44:14,263
And again, all the symptoms are here.

674
00:44:14,984 --> 00:44:17,126
There's very low payoff for play style paths.

675
00:44:18,002 --> 00:44:24,268
Principle number one, perception of distance, is violated with the playstyle up above, compared to the generic stealth path.

676
00:44:25,609 --> 00:44:31,474
We also violate principle number two, perception of exclusivity.

677
00:44:32,175 --> 00:44:40,161
Starting at entrance number two, players will inevitably see where entrance number one, basically if they hadn't used their skill check, would have started.

678
00:44:43,750 --> 00:44:48,237
Now, equipped with what I had learned, I set out to apply the beats and principles.

679
00:44:48,858 --> 00:44:53,265
The second iteration of this blockout sees a small section added to the bottom right

680
00:44:53,325 --> 00:44:57,331
corner and additional passages down to the lower floor.

681
00:45:02,613 --> 00:45:04,735
But let's get through this step by step.

682
00:45:05,336 --> 00:45:06,617
First, the beat breakdown.

683
00:45:07,137 --> 00:45:09,859
You can see now the distribution between discovery

684
00:45:09,879 --> 00:45:12,541
and exploration is quite a bit more even,

685
00:45:12,642 --> 00:45:15,664
and we have room to provide meaningful rewards.

686
00:45:18,867 --> 00:45:22,329
I added additional ways for the players down to the lower floor

687
00:45:22,550 --> 00:45:24,351
with no direct line of sight to each other,

688
00:45:24,691 --> 00:45:26,833
even leading up to the passages themselves.

689
00:45:27,837 --> 00:45:31,759
At the time the player reaches any of the passages A, B, or C,

690
00:45:32,780 --> 00:45:36,321
they will have been locked into their more linear exploration beat for quite a while,

691
00:45:36,721 --> 00:45:39,223
increasing the perception of exclusivity.

692
00:45:41,084 --> 00:45:47,387
In adding the new section, I tried to enhance the perception of distance of the choices the player has in the discovery beat

