00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:33,922
since I had this discussion with some of my fellow level designers

704
00:46:34,022 --> 00:46:35,283
after getting feedback from them.

705
00:46:36,003 --> 00:46:37,865
While it's important to make sure vision

706
00:46:37,905 --> 00:46:39,746
doesn't give away how paths work,

707
00:46:40,367 --> 00:46:44,530
we can and should still carefully and consciously work with it

708
00:46:44,890 --> 00:46:47,352
to help the player, of course, build a mental map

709
00:46:47,432 --> 00:46:48,653
and navigate the space better.

710
00:46:49,816 --> 00:46:55,019
In each exploration beat, the player is able to take a peek at the room in the center of this location,

711
00:46:55,379 --> 00:47:03,423
which features a characteristic landmark to help the player understand a bit how they're moving around the location on the path they've picked.

712
00:47:04,383 --> 00:47:07,925
You also have an opportunity to do this when using the hidden passage C.

713
00:47:09,446 --> 00:47:14,808
The vision here provided, however, does not give away how the alternate paths may work.

